latestIgtvVideos.caption: You’ve probably heard their names before — Olympians @shawnjohnson and @allysonfelix made waves and earned gold in their respective sports. But, they didn’t do it alone — they had women before them to look up to and guide them. Sports journalist @mariataylor hosts a conversation between Shawn and Allyson as they talk about the power of female mentorship, and how they hope to pave the way for female athletes of the future.

latestPosts.caption:
A new 32-year study, from researchers at Harvard, Tufts, and Brigham and Women’s Hospital, suggests a link between intake of high-quality carbohydrates and healthy aging. 

The population of older adults in the U.S. is expected to double over the next four decades, making this research even more essential: The study, which looked at potential impacts of different types of carbohydrates (think: high quality vs processed and refined) on healthy aging, provides significant insights on how the specifics of diet can have implications for longevity. 

APA Citation:  Ardisson Korat, A. V., Duscova, E., Shea, M. K., Jacques, P. F., Sebastiani, P., Wang, M., Mahdavi, S., Eliassen, A. H., Willett, W. C., & Sun, Q. (2025). Dietary Carbohydrate Intake, Carbohydrate Quality, and Healthy Aging in Women. JAMA network open, 8(5), e2511056.
latestPosts.alt: Photo by AG1 on July 06, 2025. May be an image of toast and text that says 'AG1 STUDY GUIDE New research suggests that consuming gh-quality carbohydrates has been linked to healthy aging.'.

childPosts.alt: Photo by AG1 on July 06, 2025. May be an image of toast and text that says 'AG1 STUDY GUIDE New research suggests that consuming gh-quality carbohydrates has been linked to healthy aging.'.

Photo by AG1 on July 06, 2025. May be an image of 1 person, baguette, rye bread, magazine, grocery bag, newspaper and text that says 'THE RESEARCH: The study, conducted by researchers at Harvard, Tufts, and Brigham and Women's Hospital, used data from 47,513 women over a period of 32 years. Participants completed a Food Frequency Questionnaire to ascertain their carbohydrate intake.'.

Photo by AG1 on July 06, 2025. May be an image of lentils, oats and text that says 'THE DETAILS: The research explored the association between total carbohydrate intake, refined carbohydrate intake, high- quality carbohydrate intake, and dietary fiber with healthy aging. High- High-quality carbohydrates were defined as those from whole grains, fruit, vegetables, and legumes and 'healthy aging' was defined as having all the factors below: Living to the age of 70 Being free from 11 major diseases Having no impairment in memory or physical function Being in good mental health'.

Photo by AG1 on July 06, 2025. May be an image of apple, vegetable and text that says 'THE FINDINGS: Total carbohydrate intake and high-quality carbohydrate intake were both positively associated with odds of healthy aging.'.

Photo by AG1 on July 06, 2025. May be an image of fruit, vegetable and text that says 'Intake of refined carbohydrates and starchy vegetables was not associated with odds of healthy aging. Intake of total fiber from fruits, vegetables, and cereals was positively associated with healthy aging. The results were true *even after* taking into account factors like age, BMI, and overall dietary quality.'.

Photo by AG1 on July 06, 2025. May be an image of 1 person, vegetable and text that says 'THE TAKEAWAY: Dietary intake of high quality carbohydrates (think: whole grains, fruits, vegetables, and legumes) and fiber across lifespan can be influential for healthy aging.'.

latestPosts.caption: Declare independence from unhealthy holidays. Cheers.

3am. Final stage. 460km to go.

After six days of riding the original, 1903 Tour de France, my legs weren’t the only thing feeling it—my whole system was smashed 🥵😵‍💫

I @drinkag1 to support my immune health, but on rides like this, it also plays a pivotal role in helping me stay on top of gut health while constantly fuelling with simple carbs and gas station food.

It’s a small part of every day—but it plays a big role in helping me stay consistent and in achieving my goals when everything else is starting to fall apart 💪🏽💚
